Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook Weekend: The Perfect Body
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p057xshh
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 17 Jul 2017
What does it mean to have the perfect body? Victoire Dauxerre reveals the shocking truth about how she achieved the supermodel body which almost destroyed her. British artist Alison Lapper, born with no arms and shortened legs, explains how a naked statue of her inspired the world at the 2012 Paralympic games. Image: Statue of Alison Lapper on the Fourth Plinth at Trafalgar Square in London Credit: Dan Regan/Getty Images Show less